text: Trailers are cut long before final scores are recorded or even written. Studio use music they own the licensing to in trailers or license it for the trailer. THAT is why you see so many trailers using music from movies you've seen before.

This movie "Days of Future Past" was an actual comic written long ago for Xmen called "Days of Future Past."  In that comic, a young Xavier doesn't realize he will create the Xmen and do all the things he will do, and has to be told by the future wolverine, Bishop, etc, to step in to that important role.  This comic was written decades ago, so it's based on the actual comic.

text: Wolverine is one of the most pivotal characters in the Marvel universe, both for the X-Men, an Avenger, and an independent character, because he's essentially immortal, and can't be killed.  If you threw him into an active volcano, he'd essentially be kept "dead" until he managed to get free, then he'd regenerate again, from whatever was left, and be alive again.  He's important to time travel in the comics, because of this fact, because he can survive to finish the job.

text: It's set in what is known as Earth-811, from the Uncanny X-Men #141 & #142.    In this story arc, most of the Earth's mutants have been killed in the human/mutant war, due to the rapidly advancing technologies and capabilities of Bolivar Trask's Sentinels, which eventually become so powerful that virtually no one can stand against them, and they take over North America.  Wolverine, Storm, Colossus, and Kitty Pryde were the only survivors in this arc, and only Wolverine was still free.

The comic story originally dealt with the future x-men changing events in their own past to allow a different set of events to occur, thereby changing the future for the better. Thus, in terms of these films, it's either a different future being changed for the one shown thus far (X-men 1-3, Wolverine etc.) or it's them changing the X-Men 1-3/Wolverine reality for a new one. So, in Layman's terms, either it's progressing the current films or it's a reboot.

text: Well, it's become the norm, and it's been like this for a long time. Accept it. In 1989, a trailer for "Criminal Law," an obscure Gary Oldman film, was released. Jerry Goldsmith did the score but, since he was still writing it, the studio used music from Patrick Doyle's score to "Henry V." Extremely poor planning? No - it's simple practicality. Sometimes, scoring a film - or even editing it - is a down-to-the wire affair.  No one produces a score a year before there's a final edit.

She can create precipitation at higher or lower altitudes than normal, make whirlwinds travel pointing lengthwise in any direction,channel ambient electromagnetism through her body to generate electric blasts, flash freeze objects and people, coalesce atmospheric pollutants into acid rain or toxic fog.

text: *cue dramatic trailer music*  "Fox, I'd very much like to hope again. Hope that you will not fail this time around. Hope that you will not disappoint. But time and time again, you have failed - you have disappointed.  From the misuse and senseless slaughter of iconic characters to the desecration of some of the most epic storylines ever told. When will the madness end?"  *cue Inception horns*  "When will this madness end... When will this nightmare end..."  Okay, enough of that. Fox, this may be the final time that I buy tickets to watch any X-Men movie made by you guys - make it count. There's only so many chances you can make me throw money at you, hoping you'd fix your "stupid" problem.  Perhaps there is no hope, but I hope you prove me wrong.

text: Still can't get over the fact that Wolverine has aged so much to the point where he has grey hair when only about 20 years will have passed from the end of "The Wolverine" to when this movie takes place. Barely aged a day in 150 years but suddenly ages almost identical to the years that have passed. Don't care what they did in the comics by giving him silver streaks, it makes no sense and is out of place in the movies.   His hair has the same regenerative properties the rest of his body has as we witnessed in "The Wolverine" as his hair grew back immediately following getting completely burned off in the explosion. That's my main (and really only) gripe I have with this trailer. Other than that, the general idea of humans being able to create amazingly super powerful robots that can seek out and destroy mutants and have no weaknesses themselves because of some master mold is just dumb.

text: The Correct X-Men Movie Storyline Order  1. "X-Men Origins: Wolverine" When Mutants First Appeared, Logan and his Brother were born and Emma Frost was Young as well as Cyclops. Then this was the story of how a War was about to Start  between Mutants and Humans over who will rule the earth. 2. "X-Men: First Class" The Birth of Charles and Erik Aka. Professor X & Magneto and this was the beginning of a War between Mutants and Humans. Also how Cerebro was founded and was given that name then The Mutants came to The Mansion to Harness their skills and live life their. Also to start a School there while finding other Mutants. Also how "The Brotherhood of The Mutants" were born after Magneto turned Evil 3. "X-Men" "Charlies" and "Erik" grew old after an old flash back of "Erik's" terrible past and then "Rogue" appeared and she kissed a boy and almost killed him. Then This was the beginning of a raging battle between the "X-Men" vs "The Brotherhood" while trying to prevent a War "Charlies" never wanted. The we had an Asshole named "Senator Kelly" who tried to expose all the humans for being very dangerous. Also "Magneto" tried to turn Humans into Mutants The "X-Men" beaten "The Brotherhood" and put "Magneto" in "Prison".  4. "X-Men 2: United" The War Started with the fake "Senator Kelly" impersonated by "Mystique" and Also "Logan" was falling more in Love with "Gene". When thing really got out of hand when "Logan's" old boss "Striker" showed up after attacking "The Mansion". Then tried "Striker" took over The Mansion and then tried to get "Professor X" killed by his strong mind bending son. Then that's when both the "X-Men" and "Brotherhood" teamed up and went to a Damn and took down "Striker" and his "Mutants". Then "Logan" fought "Lady Deathsrtike" killed her then tied "Striker" to the "X-Jet", help to save everyone. Also "Magneto" got his revenge and basically left "Striker" for dead. text: -if you're not interested in a rant, please ignore this comment. I'm sorry in advance.-  I'm sorry but decent x-men movie my ass. Listen- I'm a huge x-men fan- but the x-men aren't freaking about Wolverine. They don't revolve around Wolverine. 2 of my personal favorite x-men, Nightcrawler and Cyclops- aren't even in this movie-because apparently they can't recast those roles- yet they can get even more characters.  I'm not gonna say I hate Wolverine- but he's not on my list of favorite superheroes- so as an x-men fan it's disappointing that it REVOLVES around Wolverine. The Avengers was great- they did that perfect. The Fantastic Four was fine. no one had the spot light any longer than the other. But the freaking x-men movies are constant- " WOLVERINE SAVE THE DAY" "WE CAN'T DO IT BUT WOLVERINE CAN" The X-men NEVER depended on Wolverine before and they never will. He's part of the TEAM. it's not "The Wolverines" it's the "X-men" and besides- He wasn't even an original X-men member- so WHY does HE get the spotlight all the time? I understand maybe ONE character getting the spotlight PER-MOVIE. But it's not even that. it's constant Wolverine screen time. Like- if we could get movies where it follows the ORIGINAL team- that would be great- But I mean, of course they're still throw some kind of Wolverine cameo in there so what ever. God, if you're gonna revolve the movie around Wolverine- Just make Wolverine 3. But don't get everyone's hopes up and call it "X-men" cause it's not.  It doesn't matter how many X-men are in the movie- if wolverine has the spotlight the entire time, like he always does, it's not gonna matter. it's still gonna be a Wolverine movie. It just upsets me that all the other movies are amazing- and then we have freaking Wolverine and a few of the X-men. like, seriously- This is enough. Just keep making the Wolverine movies. but stop calling them "X-men" cause it's disappointing every time I see that it's only about how Wolverine saves the day.

text: SPOILER SPOILER "The credits bumper jumps back to the past with a young Erik Lehnsherr (Michael Fassbender) in a ramshackle house in the desert eating dinner, clearly on the run from all the authorities who want to bring him down. While using a well outside to get some water, the young Magneto sees something fall from the night sky and crash to Earth nearby. Upon inspecting the impact zone, he encounters what is described as an "alien form" who is "towering, terrifying, with a twisted metal face and dark pits for eyes." It's Apocalypse and he says, "I have crossed rivers of time to find you." Magneto asks, "Who are you?"   The alien responds, "I am your future." Suddenly Apocalypse merges with Magneto, who screams and blasts an insane amount of energy and shockwaves around him. This energy explosion levels everything around him, with a blast radius that goes for miles. As Magneto looks at what he's done, he has a realization of the power he now holds and a villainous grin begins to form before the film cuts to black."

text: If the music company Two Steps From Hell didn't do such a great job with the music in the trailer, I would not even consider watching this film. I think that Hollywood is trying to squeeze out as much money as they possibly can from this franchise while keeping no substance and completely disregarding sequential plot order. They slap and paste a script together while blindly making minute references to the comic book so they can keep the fans "happy" because they are being "genuine" to the material. So to put it nicely I have lost faith.   But Goddamn it, Two Steps From Hell do amazing work when it comes to music and it makes a film I have no faith in seem inspiring, heart-wrenching, and beautiful.  FUCK!

text: Title Of This Comment: Random Commentaries on Youtube Layouts Overall, Addressed to Google (Now Turning Into a Corporate Douchebag by not Listening to What The Users of Their own Website Like and do not Like)  I hate how we have to choose to identify ourselves through stupid Google Plus that you also bullied us into or just keep the names of our emails as an ID in the comments section. And it's annoying, it's not something that pops up only once saying "This is the new way to identify yourself on YouTube *Completely Optional*". Noope. It's the kind that pops up _every single time_ you try to use YouTube so you eventually are forced to choose a "new identity" when we YouTube users don't have identity crises (idk what the plural for crisis is) at all and in reality just want to watch whatever the fuck we felt like watching. Goddammit. Anyway these identity things make me feel like I have to prove myself to society more or something with that lame new ID picture we have next to our usernames when we comment on videos. This isn't fucking Tumblr or Facebook, man. Nobody wants to have to actually _try_ to identify themselves as a "cool, popular, well-rounded person that society is pressuring me to be" by finding a cool picture of their interests or posting a cute selfie of themselves like those Tumblr girls do to look like they actually have social lives and aren't internet freaks. Youtube is where we just want to be slobs and get distracted from watching science videos for school and watching dumb (but adorable) cat videos for three hours instead. Youtube is where we look something up on our iPhones when we're having debates with our friends about what the lyrics of a song are or which crappy 90's band's lead singer vomited at the 1996 Superbowl halftime concert. (Youtube is like the = to Wikipedia for proving things in social situations sometimes.) I...I just...don't want to connect to people in the YouTube comments personally ight? It's supposed to be a lazy, anonymous, and convienient way to share personal comments. Why do we suddenly need to be exchanging more information about ourselves randomly by "connecting to facebook" or "sharing on Google+"?!?! Just let Youtube be what made it magical when it first started: it was a way for people to create and consume original content and exchange feedback, responses, comments, and ideas as simply thoughts and personalities instead of revealing the person, the personal identity behind the online anonymity of people's pure personalities. Ugh.

text: For those unfamiliar: Bishop the mutant was born in an alternate future where humans had more or less won the war against mutants, putting the rest in concentration camps (basically). His mutant power lets him absorb most forms of energy to increase his strength, speed, and resistance to injury. He's a deep character with a lot of history in the X-men series. However, based on IMDB, his part in this movie (portrayed by Omar Sy) appears minimal at best, which is a shame: the plotline seems ideal for Bishop to have a heavier role.

text: As someone whi grew up on not only the Xmen, but all of Marvel and DC comics, it truly saddens me to see how my characters have been protrayed in these silly and disrespectful movies. It has been said, that it is for the younger gen types that don't go back as far as others or to bring these upto date. Take a character like wolverine and build the story him since he is the popular one now. Not understanding that, it is the story that makes the character and not the other way around. For this one, Prof. X and Magneto are long dead. They are the primary threats to the Sentinels. The way back to the past was through Rayne Summers(Scott and Jean's daughter) and Kitty Pryde. It is possible because of Pryde's phasing power. Brian Singer repairing his bad, awful and dreadful first movies? He is building on it and all of you are falling for is. If Disney can get just half of their stories right, at least this jerk can try!

text: In my Overrall opinion on the change of kitty pryde to wolverine was completely sexist and embarrassing. Why I say embarrassing is beacsue there excuse so totally immature! Saying Oh "Wolverine is the most beloved character" is basically in my opinion another way of suger-coding saying that it should be a male role model with More experience. Why make a movie about the xmen original story if basically the whole entire movie is going to be changed? as a kitty pryde fan I was completely furious when I heard about this sudden change, and then it caused me to hate the wolverine character more then I had already did so. I agree with other peoples opinions saying that they over use wolverine as the main character in every movie. in My honest opinion I don't know why people like wolverine that much anyway! hes basically a male version of a badass cat. When I say they focus on him to much is like for example...- the story between phoenix "jean grey' and scott summers was one of the most important more cared about scenario in the xmen franchise and yet there hasn't been a movie about them, instead they put out a movie such as wolverine origens which really wasn't all that important and cared for. Back on the main topic, they could've made some adjustments that could still allow ellen page or kitty pryde to still be the leading character such as drag the time line earlier or something so she could actually be alive (if they could make a drastic move like replacing her completely the they could've done something like this) but instead on actually giving her a chance in the movie they completely replaced her. And anyone saying that main characters have to be well known are lying. If you look at first class Mystique, Banshee, pixie, havoc etc. weren't really known characters but they got to play a major role in the film portrayed as main characters. I just think this decision was utterly immature and stupid.

text: Movie was a bit of a disappointment. Really only 5 mutants in this movie; wolverine, mystique, young magneto, young charles xavier and beast.They centered this around wolverine. Hugh Jackman pretty much was the star. Could've easily been another wolverine movie. Disappointing lack of action scenes. Less than 5 minutes of Storm and colossus, everybody else had like 10 second cameos including cyclops and jean/phoenix. Sentinals didn't look anything like the comics/cartoon and were a bit too small (they're supposed to be almost giants). A positive was Jen Lawrence in just body paint, but that didn't warrant the $20 to see it in 3d. I wanted to love it but came away feeling they could've done so much more and feel a bit unsatisfied. I feel like they make the trailers to these movies first and then slap together the movie afterward.

I can't believe your view of a film can be changed by seeing a favourite character in a relatively small role (Kitty Pryde had very little screen time, that would most likely be the same with Phoenix, and the girl you thought was Scarlett Witch  was only in the movie for a few)

text: Spoilers ahead...  A lot of people are excited about how DoFP essentially retcons X3 out of existence, but is anyone interested in speculating on exactly HOW the new timeline Wolverine helped create differences from the previous movies?  Just a few speculations...  Xavier snapped out of his depression much earlier in this new timeline than he probably did in the old one (if what he said in the original X-Men movie about Scott, Jean, and Storm being his "first" students was true, he probably didn't reopen the school in the original timeline until the 1990s). Thus, he'll be able to re-start the X-Men earlier and grow into a more effective leader.  Xavier read Wolverine's mind and saw key events of the old timeline (including the Dark Phoenix saga) and spent the next fifty years altering events to prevent certain tragedies. Specifically, he helped a young Jean Grey ACCEPT her full powers as Phoenix (rather than suppressing them as he did in the original timeline) which kept her from ever developing her Dark Phoenix persona and killing all those people (instead she likely helped save more people with her full power). This also basically saves his life since she won't kill him.  Despite his need to alter events, this new Xavier may be slightly less manipulative than the previous Xavier since he learns how dangerous it can be to try and control a person (like Mystique) and how important it is to let them make their own decisions.  Xavier also found and took in a young Leech before government scientists could capture him and use his genes to create the mutant "cure" that robbed mutants of their powers in X3. Thus, Mystique, Rogue, and Magneto never lost their powers -- at least not via the "cure"  Mystique broke ties with Magneto at the end of DoFP, making it unlikely they'll have the master-servant relationship of the original trilogy (I'm speculating that in the original timeline where she was captured after killing Trask she was lobotomized by scientists who used her brain tissue to study her mutant powers. Magneto then "rescued" her and took advantage of her brain damage to turn her into the silent killer from the original X-Men trilogy, which is why she doesn't have any problem putting Xavier into a coma in the original film -- she might not even remember him).  In this new timeline, she probably became a more independent character who doesn't subscribe to either Xavier or Magneto's ideologies -- although she might be more open to becoming a freelance covert operative of Xavier's since she does reconcile with him a bit at the end. (Maybe the plot of a solo Mystique movie?)  Wolverine, sadly, will probably have to go through most of the tragedies he lived through in the old timeline (including the adamantium bonding) -- but he'll have Xavier secretly keeping an eye on him for the day when he once again rejoins the X-Men.  Magneto will probably be responsible for even more atrocities than he performed in the original timeline (largely because Xavier and Wolverine helped break him out of prison possibly years before he was supposed to have escaped). Thus, mutant tensions might actually RISE for a while -- necessitating the earlier formation of the X-Men.

text: *PLEASE ANSWER THE QUESTIONS FOR ME, I AM A HUGE X-MEN FAN, BUT I NEED ANSWERS NOW. THANK YOU A LOT IF YOU CAN ANSWER.* Don't tell me to watch the old films because I've just watched them ALL in one week, so I quite remember every detail of the seven films. (I've also watched the old films several times a few years ago, but I did re-watch them recently)  1) Why is Charles Xavier alive? (You mean to tell me he's alive because he transferred his mind into a person's body, which is explained in X3, the question is, his body is buried, so even if his mind still exists, the body should be another individual's body). The credits of The Wolverine shows that Xavier is alive and Wolverine is shocked to see him, but Charles just said "You're not the only one here. There are somethings that you don't understand) WHICH STILL DOES NOT EXPLAIN WHY HE IS ALIVE.  2) How does Magneto get his power back? If you mean to tell me in X3, he got his power back from the chess play, okay don't reply me. If you have new answers, I would be very glad to hear them.  3) Why does Wolverine has adamantium claws and his healing powers again? In The Wolverine which takes place after X3, before Days of Future Past, his adamantium *AND HEALING POWERS* were extracted by The Silver Samurai. Therefore, by right he should have only bone claws now.  4) If Mystique kills Trask incident happens after First Class, before X1, does that mean her ability is restored? Because in X3 she lost her ability due to a "mutant cure" being shot and injected to her. Also why is she doing things alone without Magneto knowing while killing Trask? According to First Class, she's not doing things alone but she's on the Magneto team.

text: X-men2 a more menacing Sentinel is used in the Danger Room. Yet in the 2nd solo Wolverine movie Professor X and Magneto had to warn Wolverine of a danger, in which they all should have known already since big gigantic robots attacking them was a scenario that they trained to handle... (you would think professor x and magneto would tell wolverine in the solo wolverine movie "hey we need to find that leech kid or the formula for the cure... because there's this threat.. and the sentinels are more advance.. and hey maybe we can use it to our advantage.." Because also... how could professor x not know about the sentinels unless he did come from the future or read the future through a vision.. right?)  Leech (X-men 3) could have been used to destroy the organic future Sentinels with mutant powers.. I would think Magneto, Professor X and the countless mutants involved would have realized he can be used to mask their powers or against the sentinels. The "cure" could have been used against the organic sentinels to de-power in order to be destroyed.  (Wouldn't you think future sentinels would have been armed with the Cure ???)  Apocalypse was not affected in the time travel changes. Since he is the first mutant, invincible and most powerful he was not even seen at all in the future. The sentinels past or future should be able to track him in his slumber, because if the sentinels couldn't track him would that mean sleep helps mutants be hidden?    Rogue will be in the future re-release... But she never touched Ms. Marvel (fox has no rights to her) so most likely she shouldn't be alive since her character has been weak in previous movies. Her gaining other powers is always temporary in the film. If she were alive you would think Rogue could be used to merge Professor X and Kitty Prydes power together to bring back Wolverine in the past since. Which makes no sense by the way since it's similar to thinking about what if I changed the past in mind yet nothing changes in reality.    Nimrod should have been used in the movie and other extreme sentinels.. I would think there would be adamantium made Sentinels.. Hell wouldn't they be able to make themselves adamantium too since they gained and enhanced mystques powers.  Sentinels in the future should be near invincible after gaining an unlimited amount of powers, still though they shouldn't be able to destroy Apocalypse.   Somehow Magneto in the past controlled the 1st generation sentinels by CPU also?! He was able to control their framework but also CPU?!   I'm over Mags being the bad guy then good guy over and over.. Wolverine always having to save the day, which is a spoiler of course. The director introducing the new mutants we want to see yet kill them off quickly or no care in the world besides eye candy...  I could comment more but I really shouldn't..

text: Saw this movie for the first time yesterday on TV.   Two observations : Charles Xavier died in Last Stand, so how is he alive in this one ? Mystique was also very much alive in the original trilogy, So if she was captured and dissected to create the sentinels, then she should not have been in the original Trilogy, and the Sentinels should have been. If this is supposed to be a continuation of the original trilogy, then please writers, stick with the story line and history of it.   Oh, and DNA sequencing was very very difficult in the early 70s.   But ignoring all this, I guess it was an OK movie, but it lacked the exploration of the dark side of being an X-men like the original trilogy and those that hated them. Too Politically correct in my opinion, and was only a vehicle to get the wolverine character to join up with the new cast even if it is for only one movie.

text: I think this movie is one of the great comic-book films of 2014 which made the year one of the best for the genre after one of the worst. While I didn't hate _Iron Man 3_ and _Thor: The Dark World_ , I still think they are the weakest of the MCU, and I was abhorred by _Man of Steel_ . Then there was the disappointment that was _Batman: Arkham Origins_ . Then there was 2014. We got two of the MCU's best with _Captain America: The Winter Soldier_ and _Guardians of the Galaxy_ , then of course, this film. A film that undid all the damage caused by _X-Men: The Last Stand_ , and provided a different take on one of the best messages any film can deliver. There is no future but the one we create for ourselves. We me may not be able to change the past, but we are certainly able to determine the future.

text: The main problem with time travelling movies is that they mess up any kind of coherence for future sequels. Now things that happened in previous movies didn't actually happen. Not to mention, if going back in time is possible, then everything that happens in any movie is potentially irrelevant, because there can always be another time travel and change things again. One of the main reasons that TV show Heroes from the early 2000's lost its audience and got cancelled was because of time travelling. It is impossible to keep continuity for too long with time travelling stories, it all becomes confusing and detached. And, as far as this X Men movies series, there's a total gap with no explanation between Days of Future Past and Logan. They simply decided to throw away any attempt of continuity and simply made Logan and Xavier weak losers.

In all the Marvel films I’ve seen the only emotional scene I can think of that made me feel for the characters is scarlet witch sacrificing Vision and Peter holding onto Tony. That took 10yrs to make me feel for them. Every X-Men movie that was made I felt for the characters.  The discrimination they had to endure and the losses they had to over come with impactful moments. I will miss Fox’s vision. They put the X-Men in the REAL world with REAL problems and not a lot of people understand that. However, I know Disney will show the strength of the characters that Fox failed to do.

I understand many changes are often made by the filmmakers.  In the comic, the future daughter of Cyclops named Rachel uses her ability to send Kitty Pryde into the past.  In the movie, it’s never clearly stated how Kitty Pryde has the ability to send Logan back through time?  His consciousness.  She can phase through walls.   How is it she can do the time thing?  Nobody in the movie anywhere explains this?  A secondary mutation?  Like Emma Frost...telepath then ability to turn skin to diamond.  Did I miss something?  Anyone who knows please chime in.
